== Dough ==

In a liquid measuring cup or small bowl, combine @whole milk{1%cup}, @warm water{1/2%cup}, @unsalted butter{1/4%cup}(melted), and @sugar{1/4%cup}.

Sprinkle @active dry yeast{2 1/4%teaspoons} evenly over the wet ingredients, stir to combine, and let stand for ~{5%minutes}, until foamy.

In a large bowl, combine @all-purpose flour{4%cups} and @kosher salt{1 1/2%teaspoons}, and stir to combine. Beat @eggs{1}(large) and then add to the bloomed yeast mixture. Pour the wet ingredients into the flour and use a knife to stir until the mixture just comes together and forms a dough. Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead for ~{5-10%minutes}, or until the dough becomes smooth. Add more @all-purpose flour{=1%cups} as needed to keep the dough from sticking. To test if it’s done, tear off a small piece of dough and stretch into a thin layer. If the dough doesn’t rip, it’s ready. Or, press a finger into the dough to see if it bounces back.

Lightly grease a large glass bowl with @neutral oil{} and add the dough, cover with plastic wrap, and let rest for ~{1%hour}, or until doubled in size.

Punch down the dough, then turn out onto a floured surface. Knead for a few more minutes, just until the dough is smooth, about ~{2%minutes}.

Divide the dough into 16 equal balls, roughly the size of tangerines.

Knead the balls, gathering the edges of the dough toward the center to make a taut, round ball with a smooth top.

Place the rolls on a #baking sheet{} lined with parchment paper. Cover with plastic wrap and let rise for ~{30%minutes}.

Preheat the oven to 375˚F (190˚C).

Beat the remaining @eggs{1}(large) in a small bowl. Uncover the rolls and brush with the egg wash. Lightly sprinkle the rolls with @sea salt{}.

Bake for ~{25-30%minutes}, or until the rolls have lightly browned and doubled in size.

Enjoy!